(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a legitimated person and his spouse, children or more remote issue shall be entitled to take any interest— (a) in the estate of an intestate dying after the date of legitimation ; (b) under any disposition coming into operation after the date of legitimation ; (c) by descent under an entailed interest created after the date of legitimation ; in like manner as if the legitimated person had been born legitimate.
